Dear Governor Perdue,

Please oppose H1575, a special-interest bill that weakens
cleanup standards for polluted soil and groundwater.

I STRONGLY OPPOSE any legislation that would weaken our laws
that insure the polluter cleans up their mess!! 

H1575 would let companies that cause spills walk away without
fully cleaning up their mistakes, transferring the cost to
future generations. With spills costing much less to deal with,
corporations would spend less to avoid them, leading to more
frequent spills and accidents. Please oppose H1575.


