Dear Governor Perdue,

Please reject H1575, 'Accelerate Remediation', which weakens
standards for the cleanup of groundwater pollution.

This bill doesn't accelerate remediation; it lets polluters
shirk responsibility for spills. As North Carolina grows, we're
going to need all our groundwater resources. We can't afford to
write them off today as a subsidy to businesses that have been
careless. That's not fair to future generations, and it's not
fair to existing businesses that have taken appropriate care.
Please defeat H1575. Your voters are counting on it.


